cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on the development of a training algorithm for neural networks using optimal control theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the dynamics and stability of the algorithm, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper applies the developed methods to train neural networks with discrete weights, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the potential use of sparse weights in low-memory devices, which could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
